BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:corridor-daisy-chain-commission-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T142903Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260803
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260804
SUMMARY:Deadline: Corridor: DAISY CHAIN Artist Commission (Adur\, West Suss
 ex)
DESCRIPTION:Corridor seeks a socially-engaged artist based in the South Eas
 t of England working with moving image / lens-based media for DAISY CHAIN\
 , marking the 60th anniversary of Vera Chytilova's experimental film Daisi
 es (1966). The commissioned artist will work with a group of LGBTQIA+ youn
 g people aged 15-26 in Adur (West Sussex) to co-create new artworks: a 2-3
  minute moving image work and a series of 2D collage or mixed media artwor
 ks for public exhibition and screenings. DAISY CHAIN commissions six new a
 rtist moving image works overall (three England-based artists working with
  older women\, young women and LGBTQIA+ youth\; three artists in Czechia)\
 , developed in partnership with the National Film Museum in Prague (NaFilM
 ) and Brighton-based videoclub\, with results toured across England and Cz
 echia in 2027. EXPECTATIONS: devise about eight hands-on workshops incorpo
 rating film\, collage and mixed media (participants won't necessarily have
  an arts background)\; participate in 4-6 online peer sessions on collabor
 ative practice led by artist Annis Joslin\; complete exhibition-ready artw
 orks on time and to budget\; maintain a transparent dialogue on authorship
  with participants. Artists must have a participatory practice and experie
 nce of working creatively with young people. Note: to create a safe space\
 , workshops will not be publicly labelled as LGBTQIA+. FEE: GBP 4\,200 inc
 l. VAT plus travel and a materials budget. TIMELINE: shortlist notified 7 
 August\, online interviews 12 August 2026\; launch event in Adur/Worthing 
 March 2027. DEADLINE: 10am\, 3 August 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Corridor Proj
 ects\nLocation: Adur and Worthing\, West Sussex\, UK. Open to a socially-e
 ngaged artist based in the South East of England working with moving image
  / lens-based media.\nAward: GBP 4\,200 artist fee (inclusive of VAT) paid
  in instalments\, plus travel\, and an additional budget for materials for
  creative production\, workshops and exhibition outputs (e.g. print). No a
 pplication fee.\nDuration: September 2026 to July 2027: workshops Septembe
 r-January\, post-production to February 2027\, UK and Czech tour March-Jul
 y 2027\n\nMore: https://www.corridorprojects.org.uk/daisy-chain-commission
 ?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.corridorprojects.org.uk/daisy-chain-commission?utm_source=a
 rtificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Adur and Worthing\, West Sussex\, UK. Open to a socially-engaged a
 rtist based in the South East of England working with moving image / lens-
 based media.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:film-london-flamin-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T142903Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Deadline: Film London: The FLAMIN Fellowship 2026
DESCRIPTION:The FLAMIN Fellowship from Film London supports early-career ar
 tists working in moving image with a development bursary and a structured 
 year-long career-development programme. ELIGIBILITY: England-based moving-
 image artists with roughly 2 to 5 years of professional practice outside h
 igher education and at least two prior exhibited or screened works\; exclu
 des current students\, gallery-represented artists\, those with major solo
  institutional shows\, and film-industry professionals. Apply via the Film
  London FLAMIN Fellowship page by midnight on 1 June 2026.\n\nOrganisation
 : Film London (FLAMIN - Film London Artists' Moving Image Network)\, with 
 Arts Council England\nLocation: England\, UK (year-long programme with in-
 person workshops)\nAward: GBP 2\,500 project-development bursary per artis
 t\, plus a year-long programme of monthly in-person workshops\, 1:1 sessio
 ns with a production advisor\, screening and promotion\, and a peer commun
 ity. Stage-2 interviewees also receive a GBP 100 interview fee. No applica
 tion fee.\nDuration: One-year fellowship programme\n\nMore: https://filmlo
 ndon.org.uk/resource/apply-to-the-flamin-fellowship?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://filmlondon.org.uk/resource/apply-to-the-flamin-fellowship?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:England\, UK (year-long programme with in-person workshops)
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
